Title: Gravitational fields on a noncommutative space
Author: V. P. Nair
Comments: LaTeX, 16 pages, section 2 rewritten for clarity
Report-no: CCNY-HEP-01/10
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B651 (2003) 313-327
\\
  Noncommutative three-dimensional gravity can be described in terms of a
noncommutative Chern-Simons theory. We extend this structure and also propose
an action for gravitational fields on an even dimensional noncommutative space.
The action is worked out in some detail for fields on a noncommutative ${\bf
CP}^2$ and on $S^4$.
